The article discusses the importance of small businesses in the American economy and highlights the efforts of President Trump to support and promote their growth. It mentions that 99.7% of American businesses are small businesses and nearly half of all private-sector jobs are provided by them. The article also mentions various actions taken by President Trump to support small businesses, such as cutting job-killing regulations, authorizing pipelines for energy protection, proposing tax cuts, repealing and replacing Obamacare, reducing red tape, rolling back Dodd-Frank, and investing in infrastructure. The author expresses confidence in President Trump's leadership and believes that small businesses will continue to contribute to the economy and create a brighter future for their communities and the country.